==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪz|-eɪz]]

===Noun===

'''glaze'''

#The vitreous coating of pottery or porcelain; anything used as a coating or color in glazing. See Glaze, v. t., 3.
# ([[Meteorology]]) A smooth coating of [[ice]] formed on objects due to the [[freezing]] of [[rain]].

[[Category:Weather]]
[[Category:Meteorology]]

===Verb===

'''to glaze'''

#To become glazed of glassy.
#Broth reduced by boiling to a gelatinous paste, and spread thinly over braised dishes.
#A glazing oven. See Glost oven.
#In painting, to apply a thin, transparent layer of color.

'''Translations'''
*Portuguese: veladura
*Spanish: veladura
*Italian: velatura

